observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the accounting and reporting guidelines on the Local Roads Asset Management System outlined in COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015 be strictly adhered to, by requiring the following officials to: (a) Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of the local road under its jurisdiction and submit a report thereon;

The Municipal Accountant to prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of depreciation and disclose the road network system in the Notes to the Financial Statements; 

The General Services Officer to maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map, keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card, as well as prepare a Report on Local Road Network.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Issue a directive to all Heads of Offices in the LGU instructing that receipt and deliveries of all procured supplies and materials should be centralized and handled by the Supply Officer only for monitoring and proper recording of deliveries by the said office;
Designate an Inspection Officer and an authorized representative who will conduct inspection of all deliveries of supplies.
We also recommended that, in subsequent procurement, the Supply Officer:
Issue a pre-numbered approved Requisition and Issue Slip upon release of any kind of supplies and materials to the end-users;
Prepare the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) duly supported with pre-numbered RIS issued during each month and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant every 1st week of the month to reduce his accountability, and;
Maintain Stock Cards and record all supplies upon receipt of deliveries supported with the Acceptance and Inspection Report.
Further, we recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
Record issued supplies in the appropriate expense account based on the  SSMI and RIS from the Supply Officer, and;
Prepare and maintain Supplies Ledger Cards to record receipts, issuances and balances of supplies procured by the LGU. The SLC must be properly posted and kept updated always to support the Inventory account in the books of the LGU.
Lastly, we recommended that the Inventory Committee conduct a  physical count of all inventory items every end of the year and submit the RPCI to the Municipal Accountant for reconciliation with the balances in the Supplies Ledger Card.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor issue a directive to:
Require the officials who received the cash donations to prepare a report on how the funds were utilized and to turn-over to the Municipal Treasure any unused amounts for the issuance of Official Receipt;
Require the officials who received donations in-kind to prepare a report on the items received in CY 2020, to whom it was issued and whether there are balances still on hand;
Designate a specific official to take charge of donations, either in cash and in kind, who will maintain the necessary records and prepare the Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances.

We recommended that the: Municipal Engineer ascertain the actual weather condition existing in the project site through the Project Engineer In-charge where the projects are implemented and consider other documentary evidence prior to approval of the contractor’s request for time extension of work;]



Management strictly adhere to the rules and regulations on the grant of time extension of work in accordance with Items 10.2 and 10.5 of Annex E of the Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations (RIRR) of RA No. 9184;



Management should observe the procedure in determining the contract time or duration during the conduct of detailed engineering and disclose in the Instruction to Bidders the estimated number of rainy/unworkable days considered unfavorable for the prosecution of the works at the site before the date of bidding pursuant to Item 3(j) of Annex A of the RIRR of RA No. 9184.

We recommended that management require the: Municipal Accountant to transfer the unexpended balance of the LDRRMF to the Special Trust Fund in the Trust Fund books and revert back to the General Fund the unexpended balance of LDRRMF for CY 2013;

LDRRM Council to include in the LDRRMF Investment Plan under a separate caption, the list of PPAs charged to previous years unexpended LDRRMF balance; and

MDRRM Officer and Municipal Accountant to submit a monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of the LDRRMF within the prescribed period pursuant to COA Circular No. 2012-002.

We recommend that management:
a. Require the Accountable Municipal Officers to remit daily the full amount collected promptly and intact;
b. Enforce strictly Section 307 of RA 7160 to avoid accumulation of funds in the possession of the collecting officers and avert risk of loss or misuse of the funds.
